    <li data-comment-id="comment_blogAndPostId/blog/comment/938-1683-92" data-comment-wp-id="92" class="comment level0 calledOut author">
    	<div class="user_block">
						<!-- Comment ID is comment_blogAndPostId/blog/comment/938-1683-92 -->
            <!-- Integer Comment ID is 92 -->
			<!-- Comment parent ID is $comment.parentCommentId -->
			<!-- Comment publishDate is Wed Apr 25 14:26:52 EDT 2012 -->

			        		<a class="avatar" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/scottdecarlo/">
    				    					<img src="http://blogs-images.forbes.com/cache/gravatars/scottdecarlo_40.jpg" alt="Scott DeCarlo" />
    				        		</a>
			
						     <a class="user_name" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/scottdecarlo/">Scott DeCarlo</a><span class="desc">, Forbes Staff</span>
            
    		



    		
    		    		<span class="timestamp">1 week ago</span>
    	</div>

    	<div class="comment_content">
    		<p>Hi Crissmi,  thanks again for following up. We are working on fixing this to point to the correct company.  After you pointed this out, I reviewed this case and found out that the these two companies Hanjin Shipping (#1850) and Hanjin Shipping Holdings (#1916) are related.  Hanjin Shipping Holdings owns Hanjin Shipping, roughly 36%.  It looks like Hanjin Shipping Holdings de-consolidated Hanjin Shipping at some point in 2011 because of mandatory change in Korean IFRS accounting rules.  Worldscope database did not account for the de-consolidation and the company appears in the screen with similar figures. This explanation may be confusing.   Simply put, I should have caught this in my quality checking of the list and excluded Hanjin Shipping Holdings in our ranking. After deconsolidation, they are not big enough to qualify.  Only Hanjin Shipping (#1850) should have qualified and been included in this year&#8217;s ranking.  I apologize for the error. We will not be able to re-rank the list and/or show who would&#8217;ve been included if I had caught this before the list was published. Again, I apologize for the error.</p>

    	</div>

		
