    <li data-comment-id="comment_blogAndPostId/blog/comment/938-1683-94" data-comment-wp-id="94" class="comment level0 collapsable">
    	<div class="user_block">
						<!-- Comment ID is comment_blogAndPostId/blog/comment/938-1683-94 -->
            <!-- Integer Comment ID is 94 -->
			<!-- Comment parent ID is $comment.parentCommentId -->
			<!-- Comment publishDate is Wed Apr 25 22:50:32 EDT 2012 -->

			        		<a class="avatar" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/lovesdos/">
    				    					<img src="http://blogs-images.forbes.com/cache/gravatars/lovesdos_40.jpg" alt="lovesdos" />
    				        		</a>
			
			               	<a class="user_name" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/lovesdos/">lovesdos</a>
            
    		



    		
    		    		<span class="timestamp">1 week ago</span>
    	</div>

    	<div class="comment_content">
    		<p>your data confirms my point that china will not surpass the united states in the lifetime of my great grandchildren and my 15 grandchildren are just getting started. of the 2000 companies, the united states has 26.2% and Japan has 12.9%. Japan has 49% of what we have. china has 6.8% or 53% of japan. i assume from the article that uk is fourth with 93 companies or 4.65% or 68% of china. the soviet union, a couple of decades ago, was going to surpass the united states according to the russians and our own doom and gloom boys. it never even came close. china will grow but so will we. actually size is important and china looks better on that metric. the first company is vastly bigger than the 2000th. we have five of the top 10 (number 1, 2, 3, 8, and 9) china has two (number 5 and 7). of the top 25 we have 9 or 36% and china has 6 or 24%. All of china&#8217;s six are either banks or oil companies. Of our 9, 2 are oil companies and 3 are banks.  some day china may surpass us in gdp but it will never surpass in per capita gpd. by the way, for what it is worth the reason is that we are close to being a market economy and china is close to being a command economy.</p>

    	</div>

		
